msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/airstrike"
msgid "IL-2 Airstrike"
msgstr "Ataque aéreo de Il-2"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/date"
msgid "March 13th, 1945 · Outskirts of Sarajevo, Yugoslavia"
msgstr "13 de marzo de 1945 - Afueras de Sarajevo, Yugoslavia"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/music"
msgid "Play music (loudspeaker)"
msgstr "Reproducir música (altavoz)"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/music_hint"
msgid ""
"The loudspeaker on the Sherman can be used to raise the morale of our troops "
"by playing music."
msgstr ""
"El altavoz del Sherman puede utilizarse para elevar la moral de nuestras "
"tropas poniendo música."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/name"
msgid "Yugoslavian Heroes"
msgstr "Héroes yugoslavos"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/name_big"
msgid "Yugoslavian Heroes"
msgstr "Héroes yugoslavos"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/00"
msgid ""
"Well, the weather turned out nice today. Everyone is out and about, not a "
"single fascist or villager has noticed us coming."
msgstr ""
"Hoy ha hecho buen tiempo. Todo el mundo está fuera, ni un solo fascista o "
"local se ha dado cuenta de que veníamos."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/01"
msgid "The trucks are all going to the center of town. Too many fascists."
msgstr "Los camiones van todos al centro de la ciudad. Demasiados fascistas."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/02"
msgid ""
"You have a death wish. The Germans are retreating. We want them gone, but "
"don't have to kill them; they will run away soon enough. What are you "
"playing?"
msgstr ""
"Tienes ganas de morir. Los alemanes se están retirando. Queremos que se "
"vayan, pero no hace falta matarlos, huirán pronto. ¿A qué estás jugando?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/03"
msgid "Tiger! A bloody Tiger! "
msgstr "¡Un tiger! ¡Un maldito tiger! "

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/04"
msgid "Tigers are on the menu today! "
msgstr "¡Hoy comemos tigre! "

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/05"
msgid ""
"So, comrade tank commander, what secret weapon do you have to catch the "
"Tigers from behind, huh? Maybe we can all be blown to pieces as bait while "
"you get your shit together?"
msgstr ""
"Así que, camarada comandante de tanque, ¿Qué arma secreta tienes para "
"atrapar a los Tiger por la espalda, eh? ¿Quizá deberíamos volar todos en "
"pedazos como cebo mientras te pones las pilas?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/06"
msgid ""
"Is that solid gold? And they've hoarded truckloads of that in town? How are "
"we going to get it out?"
msgstr ""
"¿Es oro macizo? ¿Y han amontonado camiones cargados de eso en la ciudad? "
"¿Cómo vamos a sacarlo?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/07"
msgid "That is... a lot of gold!"
msgstr "Eso es... ¡mucho oro!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/08"
msgid ""
"The trucks have arrived, we will begin loading them. The warehouse needs "
"protecting until we're all done."
msgstr ""
"Los camiones han llegado, vamos a empezar a cargarlos. Hay que proteger el "
"almacén hasta que acabemos."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/09"
msgid "Fascists incoming! Comrades, defend the trucks!"
msgstr "¡Llegan los fascistas! Camaradas, ¡defended los camiones!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/fighter/10"
msgid ""
"Well comrades, I have the distinct sensation that the war ends here and now "
"for me. I hope not to see you again too soon, but it was an honor to "
"liberate the motherland with you all these years."
msgstr ""
"Bueno camaradas, tengo la clara sensación de que la guerra termina aquí y "
"ahora para mí. Espero no volver a veros demasiado pronto, pero ha sido un "
"honor liberar la patria con vosotros todos estos años."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/01"
msgid ""
"Yup, but the Germans are all over the place. Trucks are going in but not "
"coming out. Something about this stinks! We need to find out what the "
"fascists are hoarding here."
msgstr ""
"Sí, pero los alemanes están por todas partes. Los camiones entran pero no "
"salen. ¡Hay algo que huele mal aquí! Tenemos que averiguar qué están "
"acaparando aquí los fascistas."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/02"
msgid ""
"Hmm. It looks like one of those trucks broke down up ahead. I say we take a "
"look at their cargo."
msgstr ""
"Mmm. Parece que uno de esos camiones se ha estropeado ahí delante. Yo digo "
"que echemos un vistazo a su carga."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/03"
msgid ""
"My friend, this goes beyond liberating our country from the fascist yoke. "
"The Germans are taking valuables with them. This particular convoy seems "
"heavily protected."
msgstr ""
"Amigo mío, esto va más allá de liberar a nuestro país del yugo fascista. Los "
"alemanes se llevan objetos de valor. Este convoy en particular parece "
"fuertemente protegido."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/04"
msgid "Heads up, dead north! "
msgstr "¡Cuidado, al norte! "

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/05"
msgid ""
"Don't panic. The Tigers are vulnerable in close quarters. We'll outflank "
"them and attack them from behind. Whatever they are safeguarding in this "
"town must be very valuable if tigers are strolling around."
msgstr ""
"Que no cunda el pánico. Los tiger son vulnerables a corta distancia. Los "
"flanquearemos y atacaremos por la espalda. Lo que sea que estén "
"salvaguardando en esta ciudad debe de ser muy valioso si hay tiger "
"paseándose por ahí."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/06"
msgid "Well, well. Now that's something worth guarding with Tigers."
msgstr ""
"Vaya, vaya. Eso sí que es algo que merece la pena vigilar con los Tiger."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/07"
msgid "Comrade, do you know anyone who can help us extract these valuables?"
msgstr ""
"Camarada, ¿conoces a alguien que pueda ayudarnos a extraer estos objetos de "
"valor?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/08"
msgid ""
"I checked the documents in the vehicle and they were heading towards the "
"farmers' warehouse in the center of town. It makes sense; it's a large "
"building. That is where we will find our treasure. Let's move out!"
msgstr ""
"Comprobé los documentos del vehículo y se dirigían al almacén de los "
"agricultores, en el centro de la ciudad. Tiene sentido; es un edificio "
"grande. Allí es donde encontraremos nuestro tesoro. ¡En marcha!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/09"
msgid ""
"Yeah, well, this gold is useless unless we can get it out of here. The "
"Germans clearly want to take it with them, so we need to act swiftly. Secure "
"the village! Comrade tank commander, call your friends up."
msgstr ""
"Sí, bueno, este oro es inútil a menos que podamos sacarlo de aquí. Está "
"claro que los alemanes quieren llevárselo, así que tenemos que actuar con "
"rapidez. ¡Asegurad la aldea! Camarada comandante de tanque, llama a tus "
"amigos."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/10"
msgid ""
"Comrades, I need a thorough search. I don't want a single fascist left in "
"this village compromising our operation. We need those trucks coming in safe "
"and sound."
msgstr ""
"Camaradas, necesito una búsqueda exhaustiva. No quiero que quede ni un solo "
"fascista en esta aldea que comprometa nuestra operación. Necesitamos que "
"esos camiones lleguen sanos y salvos."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/11"
msgid "Damn it! We failed to clear the town!"
msgstr "¡Maldita sea! ¡No hemos conseguido despejar la ciudad!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/12"
msgid ""
"Comrades, set up a defensive perimeter around the warehouse! The gold will "
"take time to load, and the Germans will want it back!"
msgstr ""
"¡Camaradas, estableced un perímetro defensivo alrededor del almacén! El oro "
"tardará en cargarse, ¡y los alemanes querrán recuperarlo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/13"
msgid "No! We've lost too many transport trucks!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡Hemos perdido demasiados camiones de transporte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/14"
msgid "Spread out and take ambush positions!"
msgstr "¡Dispérsense y prepárense para hacer una emboscada!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/15"
msgid ""
"We don't have supplies. I wonder whether we should look out for German "
"supply convoys. At least one of them will be bound to be retreating westward."
msgstr ""
"No tenemos suministros. Me pregunto si deberíamos estar atentos a los "
"convoyes de suministros alemanes. Al menos uno de ellos se retirará hacia el "
"oeste."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/16"
msgid ""
"Comrade tank commander. The uniforms and the weaponry, I do understand. But "
"is there a particular reason to take a Tiger tank with you too?"
msgstr ""
"Camarada comandante de tanque. Lo de los uniformes y el armamento, lo "
"entiendo. Pero, ¿hay alguna razón en particular para llevar también un "
"tanque Tiger?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/leader/17"
msgid ""
"The fuel system is junk. It smells of fuel a mile away. The transmission is "
"falling to pieces. You have no spare parts and huge German markings to "
"attract friendly fire!"
msgstr ""
"Las líneas de combustible son basura. Huele a combustible a la legua. La "
"transmisión se cae a pedazos. No tiene piezas de repuesto y tiene enormes "
"marcas alemanas para atraer el fuego amigo"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/01"
msgid ""
"Now then. Tell me, comrades, what's on the menu today? How can the glorious "
"Red Army be of assistance?"
msgstr ""
"Pues bien. Decidme, camaradas, ¿qué hay hoy en el menú? ¿En qué puede "
"ayudarnos el glorioso Ejército Rojo?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/02"
msgid "Oh man... nobody said anything about them Tigers!"
msgstr "Oh, tío... ¡nadie ha dicho nada de que hubiera Tiger!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/03"
msgid ""
"Always with the pessimistic attitude, Iosif... I'll tell you what we do. We "
"have a loudspeaker, and when we go into battle, we like to play music very "
"loud... it kind of calms us down."
msgstr ""
"Siempre con la actitud pesimista, Iosif... Te diré lo que vamos a hacer: Con "
"este precioso altavoz pondremos música muy alta cuando estemos peleando, "
"cómo nos gusta."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/04"
msgid ""
"Alright, let's find out what those Fascists have got. My guys here in the "
"back are ready."
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, averigüemos qué tienen esos fascistas. Mis hombres aquí están "
"preparados."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/05"
msgid ""
"Comrade Partisan, Always with the pessimistic attitude. Can't you enjoy the "
"fact you just became rich? Why don't you let me organise a pickup?"
msgstr ""
"Camarada partisano, siempre con esa actitud pesimista... ¿No puedes "
"disfrutar del hecho de que te acabas de hacer rico? ¿Por qué no me dejas "
"organizar una recogida?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/06"
msgid ""
"Sure thing. Let's find out where the Fascists keep the gold, clear the area, "
"and I'm sure I could persuade some comrades to come along with transports. "
"The war has been very tough on all of us. The thought of returning to the "
"Urals emptyhanded seems rather sad, you know?"
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto. Averigüemos dónde guardan el oro los fascistas, despejemos la "
"zona y seguro que puedo convencer a algunos camaradas para que vengan con "
"ayuda para transportarlo. La guerra ha sido muy dura para todos nosotros. La "
"idea de volver a los Urales con las manos vacías me parece bastante triste, "
"¿sabes?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/07"
msgid "Yes, Comrade..."
msgstr "Sí, camarada..."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/08"
msgid "(on radio) Gav-gav, gav-gav!!"
msgstr "(radio) ¡¡¡Gav-gav, gav-gav!!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/09"
msgid ""
"(on radio) No, I'm not trying to be funny. Listen, I need a favour. How soon "
"can you come here with, say... 10 empty trucks?"
msgstr ""
"(radio) No, no intento hacerme el gracioso. Escucha, necesito un favor. "
"¿Cuánto tardarías en venir aquí con, digamos... 10 camiones vacíos?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/10"
msgid ""
"(on radio) Listen, I need you here round about now, I'm about to cut you "
"into a very good deal, if you don't want it, then you're out, I can find 10 "
"trucks almost anywhere."
msgstr ""
"(radio) Escucha, te necesito aquí ahora mismo, estoy a punto de hacerte un "
"buen negocio, si no lo quieres, estás fuera, puedo encontrar 10 camiones "
"casi en cualquier sitio."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/11"
msgid ""
"Yeah, just as I thought. Alright, comrades, listen up! 6 minutes for our "
"trucks to come from the southeast, secure the town!"
msgstr ""
"Sí, tal y como pensaba. Muy bien, camaradas, ¡escuchad! 6 minutos para que "
"lleguen nuestros camiones desde el sureste, ¡asegurad la ciudad!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/12"
msgid ""
"Alright, comrades, I have gotten us some air support over my portable radio. "
"It seems our air force guys have nothing better to do than accept tasking "
"from a low-life tank driver."
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, camaradas, he conseguido apoyo aéreo a través de mi radio. Parece "
"que nuestros aviadores no tienen nada mejor que hacer que aceptar la misión "
"de un tanquista de poca monta."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/13"
msgid "Alright, here goes nothing, let's see what our planes can do!"
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, aquí no pasa nada, ¡vamos a ver lo que pueden hacer nuestros "
"aviones!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/14"
msgid "Calling in an airstrike!"
msgstr "¡Pidiendo un ataque aéreo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/15"
msgid ""
"Calling in an IL-2. One thousand seven hundred horsepowers of goodness and "
"some big bombs strapped under it."
msgstr ""
"Viene un IL-2. Mil setecientos caballos de potencia de la buena y algunas "
"bombas grandes atadas debajo."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/16"
msgid "Hm. Definitely an anti-social type."
msgstr "Hm. Definitivamente un tipo antisocial."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/17"
msgid "It is a beautiful tank."
msgstr "Es un tanque precioso."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/narrator/tanker/18"
msgid ""
"Why is everyone so damn negative around here? Can't we just take a moment to "
"delight ourselves with the prize we have collected?"
msgstr ""
"¿Por qué todo el mundo es tan condenadamente negativo por aquí? ¿No podemos "
"tomarnos un momento para deleitarnos con el premio que hemos recogido?"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Great job! Who would ever have thought you’d emerge a millionaire? This "
"victory is proof that you should never let them negative waves win."
msgstr ""
"¡Gran trabajo! ¿Quién iba a pensar que te harías millonario? Esta victoria "
"es la prueba de que nunca debes dejar que ganen las ondas negativas."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"What happened? Did you not watch the 1970 movie Kelly’s Heroes? Watch it, "
"and try again."
msgstr ""
"¿Qué ha pasado? ¿No has visto la película de 1970 Los violentos de Kelly? "
"Mírala e inténtalo de nuevo."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/place"
msgid "Elements of the Yugoslav People's Liberation Army"
msgstr "Elementos del Ejército Popular Yugoslavo de Liberación"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/story"
msgid ""
"It’s 1945, and the Germans are retreating from Yugoslavia. \n"
"Having lost the easier withdrawal route through Serbia, they secure the more "
"difficult passage through Kosovo, Sandzak, and Bosnia. They even score a "
"series of temporary successes against the People's Liberation Army. \n"
"In early March, the Germans move troops from southern Bosnia to support an "
"unsuccessful counter-offensive in Hungary, enabling the People’s Liberation "
"Army to attack the weakened German positions.  \n"
"Today, you are looking for Germans while driving through the beautiful "
"Yugoslavian landscape. \n"
"Whatever you do or find, just make sure you avoid them negative waves, and "
"you’ll be fine.\n"
"\n"
"Good luck!"
msgstr ""
"Es 1945 y los alemanes se retiran de Yugoslavia.\n"
"Habiendo perdido la ruta de retirada más fácil a través de Serbia, aseguran "
"el paso más difícil a través de Kosovo, Sandzak y Bosnia. Incluso logran una "
"serie de éxitos temporales contra el Ejército Popular de Liberación.\n"
"A principios de marzo, los alemanes desplazan tropas del sur de Bosnia para "
"apoyar una contraofensiva infructuosa en Hungría, lo que permite al Ejército "
"Popular de Liberación atacar las debilitadas posiciones alemanas.  \n"
"Hoy, estás buscando alemanes mientras conduces por el hermoso paisaje "
"yugoslavo.\n"
"Hagas lo que hagas o encuentres lo que encuentres, asegúrate de que evitas "
"sus ondas negativas y todo irá bien.\n"
"\n"
"¡Buena suerte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task1"
msgid ""
"Inspect the broken-down vehicle to find what the Germans are transporting."
msgstr ""
"Inspecciona el vehículo averiado para averiguar qué transportan los alemanes."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task2"
msgid "Secure the warehouse containing the gold."
msgstr "Asegura el almacén que contiene el oro."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task3"
msgid ""
"Clear the village of Germans so the transports can safely come in to collect "
"the gold."
msgstr ""
"Limpia la aldea de alemanes para que los transportes puedan entrar con "
"seguridad a recoger el oro."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task4"
msgid ""
"Protect the trucks from German counter-attacks while the gold is being "
"loaded. At least 5 tucks must survive."
msgstr ""
"Protege los camiones de los contraataques alemanes mientras se carga el oro. "
"Al menos 5 camiones deben quedar funcionales."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task_opt_sherman"
msgid "Keep the Sherman operational."
msgstr "Mantén el Sherman operativo."

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task_secret"
msgid "Secret objective #1"
msgstr "Objetivo secreto nº 1"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/task_secret_completed"
msgid "Secret objective #1: Intercept and capture the supply truck"
msgstr "Objetivo secreto nº 1: Interceptar y capturar el camión de suministros"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/timer1"
msgid "The transport column will arrive in:"
msgstr "La columna de transporte llegará en:"

msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/timer2"
msgid "Time remaining to load the gold:"
msgstr "Tiempo restante para cargar el oro:"

#, boost-format
msgctxt "mission/single/06-bonus/1945_04_yugoslavia/trucks"
msgid "%1% transport trucks operational. "
msgstr "%1% camiones de transporte operativos. "
